Business Brief -- Reserve Industries Inc.:
   Loss for Year Is Reported;
   Statements Aren't Audited
Reserve said it had a net loss of $4 million, or $1.72 a
share, for the year ended Nov. 30. That compares with a
year-earlier loss of $512,654, or 25 cents a share, after an
extraordinary gain of $528,142 from tax benefits and the
redemption of debt. The 1991 loss included a $1 million
charge related to suspending operations at a subsidiary.
   Revenue was $7.2 million, down 18% from $8.8 million.